.TH "i2c_get_dma_safe_msg_buf" 9 "i2c_get_dma_safe_msg_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i2c_get_dma_safe_msg_buf \- get a DMA safe buffer for the given i2c_msg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8 *" i2c_get_dma_safe_msg_buf
.BI "(struct i2c_msg *msg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int threshold "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "msg" 12
the message to be checked
.IP "threshold" 12
the minimum number of bytes for which using DMA makes sense.
Should at least be 1.
.SH "RETURN"
NULL if a DMA safe buffer was not obtained. Use msg->buf with PIO.
Or a valid pointer to be used with DMA. After use, release it by
calling \fBi2c_put_dma_safe_msg_buf\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must only be called from process context!
